The paper deals with large scale graph generation and validation of diverse triangle statistics at edges and vertices, which falls under the category of graph theory and algorithms. Therefore, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses distributed settings and compressibility of graphs, which could fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also mentions worst-case complexity bounds, which could fall under cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Finally, the paper discusses the characteristics of real-world graphs, which could fall under cs.GR (Computer Graphics).
